32:11.613 --> 32:13.079
JOHNNY: I have a lot
of respect for the animals

32:13.081 --> 32:15.682
that I chase down,
or I harvest, or I catch.

32:15.684 --> 32:17.884
I have a large
understanding of them.

32:17.886 --> 32:20.553
Just because I use them
as a food source doesn't mean

32:20.555 --> 32:22.589
that I don't have a connection
to them in other ways.

32:24.960 --> 32:26.426
I mean, look at these,
these are beautiful.

32:26.428 --> 32:30.097
They're red, really nice meat,

32:30.099 --> 32:34.434
and what the plan is,
smoke a bunch of strips

32:34.436 --> 32:37.704
because I want to take a lot of
these up to the Arctic with me.

32:37.706 --> 32:39.906
Drying these out, it's
not gonna be a bunch of bulk,

32:39.908 --> 32:41.908
it's not gonna be heavy,
and it's gonna kind of fuel me

32:41.910 --> 32:43.577
while I hunt in the Arctic.

32:43.579 --> 32:46.246
I'll be munching on these
salmon sticks on a riverbank,

32:46.248 --> 32:50.417
around a hilltop, glassing
