getting my firewood.

41:08.216 --> 41:09.749
I know it's already there.

41:09.751 --> 41:11.484
I know that I have
enough for the winter,

41:11.486 --> 41:15.555
and that is incredibly
freeing to me.

41:15.557 --> 41:17.690
Oh, man, nice stack.

41:17.692 --> 41:20.560
GILBERT: Yeah, it's taller
than me right here.

41:20.562 --> 41:21.427
Come look.

41:21.429 --> 41:23.296
ELOVIE: And me.

41:23.298 --> 41:26.299
KALEB: Oh, boy.

41:26.301 --> 41:28.034
Last three pieces.

41:28.036 --> 41:28.901
BRITTANY: Woo-hoo!

41:28.903 --> 41:31.237
KALEB: I got
the last three pieces.

41:31.239 --> 41:32.705
BRITTANY: Yeah, baby!

41:32.707 --> 41:34.240
KALEB: And that's a wrap.

41:34.242 --> 41:37.710
We worked hard.
We got this woodshed up.

41:37.712 --> 41:39.546
We are set.

41:43.051 --> 41:44.250
JESSI: All right, so.

41:44.252 --> 41:45.518
CHRIS: That's a huge fish.

41:45.520 --> 41:50.056
JESSI: I know. That is
gonna feed us for a while.

41:50.058 --> 41:52.792
Chris and I have come
a long ways this year.

41:52.794 --> 41:56.863
A hard couple months
of trapping and a lean winter.

41:56.865 --> 42:02.068
Times like today, now it's
all culminating until tonight.

42:02.070 --> 42:06.472
We're gonna feast on this fish.

42:06.474 --> 42:08.007
CHRIS: It's good to go.

42:12.280 --> 42:13.746
JESSI: Mmm.

42:16.218 --> 42:17.584
CHRIS: So good.

42:19.354 --> 42:23.222
JESSI: I've been waiting
for this for so long.

42:23.224 --> 42:24.357
CHRIS: Wow.

42:24.359 --> 42:26.626
Takes me back to being a kid,

42:26.628 --> 42:30.496
sitting on the sandbar
with my dad, eating fish.

42:30.498 --> 42:32.599
This has just been a great trip.

42:35.169 --> 42:36.035
CHEVIE: What do you guys think?

42:36.037 --> 42:37.370
SYDNEY: Oh, it's sick.

42:37.372 --> 42:39.706
RYDER: Oh, this is so cool.

42:39.708 --> 42:42.642
CHEVIE: Home sweet home.
Good job on the tree stand.

42:42.644 --> 42:45.311
Way to whip it,
you guys worked hard.

42:45.313 --> 42:47.580
Final touch right here, okay?

42:47.582 --> 42:50.450
So, this is, this is,
this was your papa's gun rack.

42:50.452 --> 42:53.119
I had this when I was
a little kid around my house...

42:53.121 --> 42:54.187
SYDNEY: Cool.

42:54.189 --> 42:57.190
CHEVIE: and so, here's
a little bit of Papa,

42:57.192 --> 43:00.193
a little bit of
older Roaches here.

43:00.195 --> 43:04.931
You guys get to use this
your whole lives.

43:04.933 --> 43:06.599
Okay, put in
the final screws, you guys.

43:06.601 --> 43:08.935
SYDNEY: And then maybe
if we have any children,

43:08.937 --> 43:10.536
we'll give it to our children.

43:10.538 --> 43:12.939
CHEVIE: Sweet. Okay, Sydney.

43:12.941 --> 43:13.940
(drilling)

43:13.942 --> 43:17.877
Good. All right, guys.
Come over. Group hug.

43:17.879 --> 43:19.145
Love you guys.

43:19.147 --> 43:20.813
(kissing)

43:20.815 --> 43:21.881
What a big help you guys were.

43:21.883 --> 43:22.749
RYDER: Yeah.

43:22.751 --> 43:24.517
CHEVIE: Let's think
about the next project.

43:26.955 --> 43:29.689
JOHNNY: These are sacs
of salmon roe.

43:29.691 --> 43:31.090
It's just the eggs.

43:31.092 --> 43:34.293
You know, if was to just
put this stuff to the side

43:34.295 --> 43:35.895
and say, "I'll deal
with it later,"

43:35.897 --> 43:37.630
it's just gonna rot,
it's gonna spoil,

43:37.632 --> 43:40.366
so as soon I get all of
this meat, all of this fish,

43:40.368 --> 43:43.970
all of this stuff, I have
to immediately start curing it,

43:43.972 --> 43:46.973
um, start preserving it.

43:46.975 --> 43:49.642
You know, this is what it takes
to live this lifestyle.

43:49.644 --> 43:52.244
It was a good day,
got a lot done.

43:52.246 --> 43:54.246
A lot of hurdles,
a lot of challenges.

43:54.248 --> 43:55.114
It might be tiring.

43:55.116 --> 43:57.050
It might wear on me
from time to time,

43:57.052 --> 44:00.920
but, you know, there's not
a lot of instant gratification

44:00.922 --> 44:05.124
with this lifestyle, but that's
not really what I'm after.

44:05.126 --> 44:06.659
You know, I like
putting in the time.

44:06.661 --> 44:08.461
I like putting in the work,

44:08.463 --> 44:11.197
putting in the blood,
the sweat, the tears.

44:11.199 --> 44:12.398
To me, that's way more important

44:12.400 --> 44:15.601
than any paycheck I've ever
gotten or any achievement

44:15.603 --> 44:18.671
or any pat on the back
I've ever received.
